Main Menu
The main menu provides the following selection of items: \begin{description} \item[Task] Activates the task dialog, allowing tasks to be edited, saved and loaded, and for browsing waypoints by name. \item[Bugs/Ballast] Activates the bugs/ballast dialog, allowing entry of bugs and ballast percentages. \item[Pressure] Activates the pressure dialog, allowing entry of QNH pressure. \item[Logger] Turns on or off the IGC flight logger. When the logger is started, the current task is written as a declaration at the start of the logger file. A new logger file is created each time the logger is started. The logger files are written using a subset of the IGC format although the logger is not approved for verification of any IGC badge or records. \item[Settings] Provides several pages of configuration settings. Typically these settings are seldom changed after initial installation, and it is recommended they not be modified in flight. \item[Abort] Aborts or resumes the current task. \item[Status] Activates the Status dialog, giving a quick overview of system status. \item[Analysis] Activates the Analysis dialog, giving detailed analysis and statistics on relating to task performance. \item[Cancel] Returns to the map screen. \item[Exit] Quit the application. Always use this method of closing the application as it ensures that the software is terminated cleanly. \item[Edit infoboxes] This checkbox allows infoboxes to be edited. \end{description}
